          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Place</strong> the beetroot under the grill for 5 min or until it has started to release moisture, then remove the tray briefly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the halloumi sticks to the opposite side of the tray</p>\r\n<p><strong>Return</strong> the tray to the grill for a further 8-12 min or until the halloumi is golden, flipping halfway</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add the cider vinegar, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(4 tbsp)</span> olive oil, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> boiled water and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(1 tsp)</span> sugar in a small bowl</p>\r\n<p><strong>Whisk</strong> together until the sugar is dissolved - this is your dressing</p>\r\n<p><strong>Roughly</strong> chop the dill, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/484.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Place</strong> a wide-based pan over a medium heat with 1-3 tbsp olive oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the almonds, shallot and garlic and cook for 3-4 min or until browned and crispy, stirring constantly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remove</strong> the pan from the heat and mix in the cooked couscous</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> lightly with salt and pepper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
